        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 4:13PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 413 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles east of Eads, or 11 miles northeast of Collierville, moving
east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Somerville, Lagrange, Warren, Macon, Oakland, Piperton, Gallaway,
Rossville, Moscow, Williston, Grand Junction, Braden, La Grange, Yum
Yum, Belmont, Taylor Chapel, Kirk, Hickory Withe, Pattersonville, and
Fayette Corners.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
